# Done means verified on this build

This exists because "fixed" was claimed for months on mechanism-level green
(preflight passed, a unit test passed, a branch was rebuilt) while the end-to-end
outcome was still red. Mechanism-green is a proxy. It is not done.

## The one definition of done

A change is done only when **a real request completes on the live process and a
calibrated judge marks it correct, and you watched it happen** — recorded as a
build-hash-keyed receipt for the running build. Not a green meter, not a passing
unit test, not a rebuilt branch.

- The static half: `scripts/gate.sh` is green (lints + structural absences + unit
  suite).
- The runtime half: `scripts/live_meter.py` certifies a real `do_with_claude`
  request genuinely succeeded (a real tool fired, not Blocked) on the trunk build,
  and writes `data/receipts/<build_hash>.json`.
- A receipt is valid only for the exact build that produced it. Any change to the
  build (src / prompts / specs / models.yaml) changes the hash, so a stale receipt
  cannot certify a new build. The CRITICAL `deployed_trunk` gate guarantees the
  live pid IS that build, so the receipt proves the live pid.

## Don't trust boot-time, on-disk, or offline-score green

None of them is "done". If a change can be called "fixed" without a real request
passing on the live build, the meter is wrong — fix the meter, don't relax the
definition.

## Unverified counts as fail

A check that cannot honestly run is `unverified`, which counts as a failure and is
recorded + alerted — it never silently disappears and never reads as a pass.
